main method.
What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
Interface does not have any implementation of the method. But in Abstract class Some method can be implemented.
Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?
NO, because of the unimplemented method.
what is Access Specifier?
Access Specifier regulates access to classes, fields and method in java. it determine whether a field or method in a class
can be used or invoked by another method in another class or sub-class. it can be used to restrict classes.
