What is the difference between String, StringBuffer and StringBuilder?
Ans:String is immutable object, if object is created once,can not be changed object.
StringBuffer is mutable.It is Syncrinized that is thread safe.
StringBuilder is mutable but not thread safe.
What is Singleton class?
Ans:In object-oriented programming, a singleton class is a class that can have only one
object (an instance of the class) at a time.
What is Serialization and Deserialization?
Ans:Serialization is a process of converting an object into a sequence of bytes which can be persisted to a disk or
database or can be sent through streams. The reverse process of creating object from sequence of bytes is called
Deserialization.
